  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peace building and trauma healing for victims of war in Unity State South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Reduction in the level of trauma
- safe place created for women
- Active involvement of IDPs and host communities in peacebuilding
- people are resilient to violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- training of 80 women and youth in Nyal and Mayendit South on Psychosocial support
- Distribution of Emergency Sanitation and Clothing materials to the most Vulnerable women and girls, both IDPs and Host community.
- Train 6 volunteer psychosocial support facilitators on case reporting, management and case referral.
- Coaching, Mentoring and regular support for the volunteer PSS facilitators
- Conduct community awareness raising and advocacy on the problem associated with GBV in the community
- Facilitate dialogue between women and church leaders about the health and social impacts of GBV and child recruitment in the armed forces.
- train 120 young people, both boys and girls in leadership skills in nyal and mayendit.
- Organization of 4 football tournaments for young people as a gesture of reconciliation and healing measures.</narrative>
  </description>
